I've been very reluctant to post this review since I know how much small businesses rely on reviews, but I feel no other choice currently. On my recommendation we went to Crane Alley to eat. Our service was deplorable. Food order was wrong, some food came cold, and the wait staff was just terrible! I talked with the manager behind the bar, since he was only available there and could not see me or my party at our table, to explain this. He apologized about our waitress almost excusing her poor service to being new and a busier night. The management did NOTHING to rectify the experience. I was severely embarrassed and I'll never take another group I'm responsible for to this establishment again or at least till I see the management care about this experience I had. There needs to be a change in service procedures at this establishment.  In response to Crane Alley's response to this review on 4/24:  You in fact DID NOT offer any recompense for the experience my guests and I had. In speaking with the manager behind the bar, who had glasses, a nose ring and other piercings (description to give specificity when others may see you), only told me they would talk with the server. There was nothing offered in the way of free drinks, free food, or comping any part of the meal. Had that actually happened I would have likely never left the review I left. My bill was $120+. I find it very concerning you (as an establishment and representative) would dispute this review with falsehoods. I'll come in and speak with you about this in the near future and my continuing patronage.
